<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<xsl:stylesheet version="1.1"
	xmlns:xsl="http://www.w3.org/1999/XSL/Transform" xmlns:fo="http://www.w3.org/1999/XSL/Format"
	exclude-result-prefixes="fo" xmlns:fn="http://www.w3.org/2005/02/xpath-functions"
	xmlns:java="java">

	<xsl:template match="/" name="LPL-AMEND-VA">

		<fo:block>
			<xsl:call-template name="CommonHeader" />
		</fo:block>

		<fo:block text-align="center" margin-left="1.3in"
			margin-right="1.3in" font-size="12px"
			font-family="Arial, 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, sans-serif;"
			space-before="5mm" space-after="5mm" font-weight="bold">
			VIRGINIA AMENDATORY ENDORSEMENT
		</fo:block>
		<fo:block padding-left="5pt"
			font-family="Arial, 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, sans-serif;"
			font-size="10px" text-align="justify">

			<fo:block space-after="4mm">
				In consideration of the premium charged, it is agreed that:
			</fo:block>
			
			<fo:block space-after="4mm">


				<fo:list-block>
					<fo:list-item space-after="4mm">
						<fo:list-item-label>
							<fo:block>
								<fo:inline>1.</fo:inline>
							</fo:block>
						</fo:list-item-label>
						<fo:list-item-body start-indent="7mm">
							<fo:block space-after="4mm">
								Section II., Limits of Liability and Deductible, subsection A., Limits of Liability, paragraph 6., is deleted and replaced with the following:
							</fo:block>
							<fo:block>
							<fo:list-block>
							<fo:list-item>
							<fo:list-item-label>
							<fo:block>
								6.
							</fo:block>
							</fo:list-item-label>
							<fo:list-item-body start-indent="14mm">
							<fo:block>
								If the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Insurer</fo:inline> has exhausted the applicable Limit of Liability by
								payment of <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Damages</fo:inline> or <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Defense Expenses</fo:inline> or by tender of the remaining
								Limit of Liability into court, it shall have no further duties to the
								<fo:inline font-weight="bold">Insured</fo:inline> under this policy except for those provided under: (a) Section
								III., Extension of Coverage D., Extended Reporting Period Extensions;
								and (b) Section VI., General Condition D., Cancellation, Nonrenewal,
								Conditional Renewal and Loss Information.
							</fo:block>
							</fo:list-item-body>
							</fo:list-item>
							</fo:list-block>
							</fo:block>
						</fo:list-item-body>
					</fo:list-item>
					<fo:list-item space-after="4mm">
						<fo:list-item-label>
							<fo:block>
								<fo:inline>2.</fo:inline>
							</fo:block>
						</fo:list-item-label>
						<fo:list-item-body start-indent="7mm">
							<fo:block space-after="4mm">
								Section III., Extension of Coverage D., Extended Reporting Period Extensions, is amended as follows:
							</fo:block>
							<fo:block>
							<fo:list-block>
							<fo:list-item>
							<fo:list-item-label>
							<fo:block>
								a.
							</fo:block>
							</fo:list-item-label>
							<fo:list-item-body start-indent="14mm">
							<fo:block space-after="4mm">
								Subsection 2., Optional Extended Reporting Period, is deleted and replaced with the following:
							</fo:block>
							<fo:block>
							<fo:list-block>
							<fo:list-item>
							<fo:list-item-label>
							<fo:block font-weight="bold">
								2.
							</fo:block>
							</fo:list-item-label>
							<fo:list-item-body start-indent="21mm">
							<fo:block font-weight="bold" space-after="4mm">
								Optional Extended Reporting Period
							</fo:block>
							<fo:block space-after="4mm">
								Upon “policy termination”, the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Named Insured</fo:inline> shall have the right, upon
								payment of the additional premium shown in one of the options below for
								the length of time shown, to report <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Claims</fo:inline> pursuant to Section VI.,
								General Condition A., Notice of <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Claim</fo:inline> or Circumstance, paragraph 1.
							</fo:block>
							<fo:block space-after="4mm">
								For the purposes of this subsection, “policy termination” shall
								include: (i) cancellation or nonrenewal of this policy by the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Insurer</fo:inline>
								or the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Named Insured</fo:inline>; (ii) advancement of any applicable <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Prior Acts
								Date</fo:inline>; or (iii) renewal of the policy on other than a claims-made basis.
								No offer of an Optional Extended Reporting Period is required if
								cancellation or nonrenewal is due to (i) nonpayment of premium; (ii)
								failure to comply with terms or conditions of the policy; or (iii)
								fraud.
							</fo:block>
							<fo:block space-after="4mm">
								Upon “policy termination”, the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Insurer</fo:inline> shall offer in writing to the
								<fo:inline font-weight="bold">Named Insured</fo:inline> an Optional Extended Reporting Period for the duration
								and premium options indicated below. The offer shall be sent no earlier
								than the date of notification of “policy termination” and not later
								than 15 days after the “policy termination”. This right to elect an
								Optional Extended Reporting Period shall lapse unless the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Named Insured</fo:inline>
								provides the Insurer with written notice of its selection and pays the
								premium charge for the selected Optional Extended Reporting Period in
								full within 60 days of the “policy termination”.
							</fo:block>
							<fo:block>
								The available Optional Extended Reporting Periods are:
							</fo:block>
							<fo:block space-after="4mm">
							<fo:list-block>
							<fo:list-item>
							<fo:list-item-label>
							<fo:block>
								(a)
							</fo:block>
							</fo:list-item-label>
							<fo:list-item-body start-indent="28mm">
							<fo:block>
								12 months for a premium charge of 100% of the annual policy premium;
							</fo:block>
							</fo:list-item-body>
							</fo:list-item>
							<fo:list-item>
							<fo:list-item-label>
							<fo:block>
								(b)
							</fo:block>
							</fo:list-item-label>
							<fo:list-item-body start-indent="28mm">
							<fo:block>
								36 months for a premium charge of 185% of the annual policy premium;
							</fo:block>
							</fo:list-item-body>
							</fo:list-item>
							<fo:list-item>
							<fo:list-item-label>
							<fo:block>
								(c)
							</fo:block>
							</fo:list-item-label>
							<fo:list-item-body start-indent="28mm">
							<fo:block>
								60 months for a premium charge of 225% of the annual policy premium;
							</fo:block>
							</fo:list-item-body>
							</fo:list-item>
							<fo:list-item>
							<fo:list-item-label>
							<fo:block>
								(d)
							</fo:block>
							</fo:list-item-label>
							<fo:list-item-body start-indent="28mm">
							<fo:block>
								72 months for a premium charge of 250% of the annual policy premium;
							</fo:block>
							</fo:list-item-body>
							</fo:list-item>
							<fo:list-item>
							<fo:list-item-label>
							<fo:block>
								(e)
							</fo:block>
							</fo:list-item-label>
							<fo:list-item-body start-indent="28mm">
							<fo:block>
								An unlimited period for a premium charge of 300% of the annual policy premium.
							</fo:block>
							</fo:list-item-body>
							</fo:list-item>
							</fo:list-block>
							</fo:block>
							<fo:block space-after="4mm">
								Coverage under such extension of time to report a <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Claim</fo:inline> (referred to
								below as the Optional Extended Reporting Period) shall apply solely to
								negligent acts, errors or omissions in rendering <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Professional Services</fo:inline>
								committed or attempted prior to the effective date of nonrenewal or
								cancellation, whichever occurs first, and which are not otherwise
								excluded by any terms, conditions or exclusions of this policy.
							</fo:block>
							<fo:block>
								If the Optional Extended Reporting Period requested by the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Named Insured</fo:inline> is issued by the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Insurer</fo:inline>:
							</fo:block>
							</fo:list-item-body>
							</fo:list-item>
							</fo:list-block>
							</fo:block>
							</fo:list-item-body>
							</fo:list-item>
							</fo:list-block>
							</fo:block>
						</fo:list-item-body>
					</fo:list-item>
					</fo:list-block>
			</fo:block>
			<fo:block margin-top="2cm"/>
           <fo:block  font-size="9px" color="grey" text-align="left">LPL-AMEND-VA (04/17)&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
               &#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
               &#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
               &#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;Page 1 of 4</fo:block>
		</fo:block>
		<fo:block break-after="page" />
		
		<fo:block padding-left="5pt"
			font-family="Arial, 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, sans-serif;"
			font-size="10px" text-align="justify">
			
		<fo:list-block>
		<fo:list-item>
		<fo:list-item-label start-indent="21mm">
		<fo:block>
			(1)
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:list-item-body start-indent="28mm">
		<fo:block>
			the additional premium shall be fully earned by the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Insurer</fo:inline>; and
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-body>
		</fo:list-item>
		<fo:list-item space-after="4mm">
		<fo:list-item-label start-indent="21mm">
		<fo:block>
			(2)
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:list-item-body start-indent="28mm">
		<fo:block>
			the Optional Extended Reporting Period cannot be cancelled by the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Insureds</fo:inline> or the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Insurer</fo:inline>.
		</fo:block>
		<fo:block start-indent="21mm">
			The Optional Extended Reporting Period shall be effective the same day the Automatic Extended Reporting Period expires.
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-body>
		</fo:list-item>
		<fo:list-item space-after="4mm">
		<fo:list-item-label start-indent="7mm">
		<fo:block>
			b.
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:list-item-body start-indent="14mm">
		<fo:block>
			Subsection 4., Conditions for Extended Reporting Periods, shall only apply to the Non-Practicing Extended Reporting Period.
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-body>
		</fo:list-item>
		<fo:list-item space-after="4mm">
		<fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:block>
			3.
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:list-item-body start-indent="7mm">
		<fo:block space-after="4mm">
			Section III., Extensions of Coverage, is amended by addition of the following:
		</fo:block>
		<fo:block space-after="4mm">
		<fo:list-block>
		<fo:list-item>
		<fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:block font-weight="bold">
			•
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:list-item-body start-indent="14mm">
		<fo:block space-after="4mm" font-weight="bold">
			Post-Judgment Interest
		</fo:block>
		<fo:block>
			Any payments made for post-judgment interest will be in addition to the Limit of Liability.
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-body>
		</fo:list-item>
		</fo:list-block>
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-body>
		</fo:list-item>
		<fo:list-item space-after="4mm">
		<fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:block>
			4.
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:list-item-body start-indent="7mm">
		<fo:block space-after="4mm">
			Section IV., Definition E., Damages, is amended by deleting the first sentence and replacing it with the following:
		</fo:block>
		<fo:block space-after="4mm">
			<fo:inline font-weight="bold">Damages</fo:inline> means a monetary judgment (including pre-judgment interest
			awarded against the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Insured</fo:inline>), monetary award or monetary settlement
			negotiated with the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Insurer’s</fo:inline> written consent.
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-body>
		</fo:list-item>
		<fo:list-item space-after="4mm">
		<fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:block>
			5.
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:list-item-body start-indent="7mm">
		<fo:block space-after="4mm">
			Section VI., General Condition C., Action Against Insurer, is amended by addition of the following:
		</fo:block>
		<fo:block space-after="4mm">
			Notwithstanding anything in this subsection to the contrary, if
			execution on a judgment against the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Insured</fo:inline> or his/her personal
			representative is returned unsatisfied in an action brought to recover
			damages for injury sustained or for loss or damage incurred during the
			life of this policy, then an action may be maintained against the
			<fo:inline font-weight="bold">Insurer</fo:inline> under the terms of this policy for the amount of the judgment
			not exceeding the amount of the applicable Limit of Liability under
			this policy.
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-body>
		</fo:list-item>
		<fo:list-item space-after="4mm">
		<fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:block>
			6.
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:list-item-body start-indent="7mm">
		<fo:block space-after="4mm">
			Section VI., General Condition D., Cancellation and Nonrenewal, is deleted and replaced with the following:
		</fo:block>
		<fo:block>
		<fo:list-block>
		<fo:list-item space-after="4mm">
		<fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:block font-weight="bold">
			D.
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:list-item-body start-indent="14mm">
		<fo:block font-weight="bold" space-after="4mm">
			Cancellation, Nonrenewal, Conditional Renewal and Loss Information
		</fo:block>
		<fo:block>
		<fo:list-block>
		<fo:list-item space-after="10mm">
		<fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:block font-weight="bold">
			1.
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:list-item-body start-indent="21mm">
		<fo:block space-after="4mm" font-weight="bold">
			Cancellation
		</fo:block>
		<fo:block>
		<fo:list-block>
		<fo:list-item space-after="4mm">
		<fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:block>
			(a)
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:list-item-body start-indent="28mm">
		<fo:block>
			The <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Named Insured</fo:inline> may cancel this policy at any time prior to the
			expiration date of the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Policy Period</fo:inline> by providing prior written notice
			to the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Insurer</fo:inline> or by surrender of this policy to the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Insurer</fo:inline> or its
			authorized agent. If the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Named Insured</fo:inline> cancels this policy, the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Insurer</fo:inline>
			shall return 90% of the unearned portion of the premium. However, upon
			cancellation whenever the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Insurer</fo:inline> has received notice that the return
			premium has been assigned to a premium finance company, the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Insurer</fo:inline>
			shall return the gross unearned premium to such company within 30 days
			after the effective date of cancellation.
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-body>
		</fo:list-item>
		<fo:list-item space-after="4mm">
		<fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:block>
			(b)
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:list-item-body start-indent="28mm">
		<fo:block space-after="4mm">
			The <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Insurer</fo:inline> may only cancel this policy for nonpayment of premium
			or Deductible. This policy may be canceled by the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Insurer</fo:inline> by mailing or
			delivering to the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Named Insured</fo:inline>, at the address shown on the policy, or
			by delivering electronically to the address provided by the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Named
			Insured</fo:inline>, written notice of cancellation at least:
		</fo:block>
		<fo:block space-after="4mm">
		<fo:list-block>
		<fo:list-item>
		<fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:block>
			(1)
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:list-item-body start-indent="35mm">
		<fo:block>
			15 days before the effective date of cancellation for nonpayment of premium; or
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-body>
		</fo:list-item>
		<fo:list-item>
		<fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:block>
			(2)
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:list-item-body start-indent="35mm">
		<fo:block>
			45 days before the effective date of cancellation for nonpayment of Deductible.
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-body>
		</fo:list-item>
		</fo:list-block>
		</fo:block>
		<fo:block>
			Such notice shall state the specific reason or reasons of the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Insurer</fo:inline>
			for cancellation. If notice is mailed, proof of mailing shall be
			sufficient proof of mailing and the effective date of cancellation
			stated in such notice shall become the expiration date of the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Policy
			Period</fo:inline>. If the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Insurer</fo:inline> cancels this policy, the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Insurer</fo:inline> shall credit
			the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Named Insured</fo:inline> the pro rata unearned portion of the premium. Payment
			or tender of any unearned premium by the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Insurer</fo:inline> shall not be a
			condition precedent to the effectiveness of cancellation, but such
			payment shall be made as soon as practicable.
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-body>
		</fo:list-item>
		</fo:list-block>
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-body>
		</fo:list-item>
		<fo:list-item>
		<fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:block font-weight="bold">
			2.
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:list-item-body start-indent="21mm">
		<fo:block font-weight="bold">
			Nonrenewal
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-body>
		</fo:list-item>
		</fo:list-block>
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-body>
		</fo:list-item>
		</fo:list-block>
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-body>
		</fo:list-item>
		</fo:list-block>
		<fo:block margin-top="2.5cm"/>
           <fo:block  font-size="9px" color="grey" text-align="left">LPL-AMEND-VA (04/17)&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
               &#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
               &#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
               &#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;Page 2 of 4</fo:block>
		</fo:block>
		<fo:block break-after="page" />
		
		<fo:block padding-left="5pt"
			font-family="Arial, 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, sans-serif;"
			font-size="10px" text-align="justify">
		
		<fo:list-block>
		<fo:list-item space-after="4mm">
		<fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:block></fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:list-item-body start-indent="21mm">
		<fo:block space-after="4mm">
			This policy may be nonrenewed by the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Insurer</fo:inline> by mailing or delivering
			to the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Named Insured</fo:inline>, at the address shown on the policy, or by
			delivering electronically to the address provided by the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Named Insured</fo:inline>,
			written notice of nonrenewal at least 45 days prior to the expiration
			date of the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Policy Period</fo:inline>. Such notice shall state the specific reason
			or reasons of the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Insurer</fo:inline> for nonrenewal. If notice is mailed, proof of
			mailing shall be sufficient proof of notice.
		</fo:block>
		<fo:block space-after="4mm">
			Nothing in this subsection shall apply if:
		</fo:block>
		<fo:block>
		<fo:list-block>
		<fo:list-item>
		<fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:block>
			(a)
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:list-item-body start-indent="28mm">
		<fo:block>
			the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Named Insured</fo:inline> has notified orally, or in writing, the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Insurer</fo:inline>
			or its agent that it wishes this policy to be nonrenewed;
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-body>
		</fo:list-item>
		<fo:list-item>
		<fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:block>
			(b)
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:list-item-body start-indent="28mm">
		<fo:block>
			prior to the date of expiration, the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Named Insured</fo:inline> fails to accept the
			offer of the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Insurer</fo:inline> to renew this policy; or
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-body>
		</fo:list-item>
		<fo:list-item>
		<fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:block>
			(c)
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:list-item-body start-indent="28mm">
		<fo:block>
			an affiliated insurer has manifested its willingness to provide
			coverage at a lower premium than would have been charged for the same
			exposures on the expiring policy. The affiliated insurer shall manifest
			its willingness to provide coverage by issuing a policy with the types
			and limits of coverage at least equal to those contained in the
			expiring policy unless the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Named Insured</fo:inline> has requested a change in
			coverage or limits. When such offer is made by an affiliated insurer,
			an offer of renewal shall not be required of the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Insurer</fo:inline> of the
			expiring policy, and the policy issued by the affiliated insurer shall
			be deemed to be a renewal policy.
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-body>
		</fo:list-item>
		</fo:list-block>
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-body>
		</fo:list-item>
		<fo:list-item space-after="4mm">
		<fo:list-item-label start-indent="14mm">
		<fo:block font-weight="bold">
			3.
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:list-item-body start-indent="21mm">
		<fo:block space-after="4mm" font-weight="bold">
			Conditional Renewal
		</fo:block>
		<fo:block space-after="4mm">
			No “reduction in coverage” and no “insurer-initiated increase in
			premium” greater than 25% shall be effective unless the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Insurer</fo:inline>
			delivers or mails to the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Named Insured</fo:inline> at the address shown on the
			policy, or delivers electronically to the address provided by the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Named
			Insured</fo:inline>, a written notice of conditional renewal not later than 45 days
			prior to the expiration date of the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Policy Period</fo:inline>. The increase in
			premium shall be the difference between the renewal premium and the
			premium charged by the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Insurer</fo:inline> at the effective date of the expiring
			policy. Such notice shall advise the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Named Insured</fo:inline> of the specific
			reason for the increase and the amount of the increase, or, if in the
			case of a reduction in coverage, the specific reason for the reduction
			and the manner in which coverage will be reduced, or that such
			information may be obtained from the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Insurer</fo:inline> or its agent. If notice is
			mailed, proof of mailing shall be sufficient proof of notice.
		</fo:block>
		<fo:block space-after="4mm">
			For the purposes of this subsection:
		</fo:block>
		<fo:block space-after="4mm">
		<fo:list-block>
		<fo:list-item>
		<fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:block>
			(a)
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:list-item-body start-indent="28mm">
		<fo:block>
			“reduction in coverage” shall mean, but not be limited to, any
			diminution in scope of coverage, decrease in the Limit of Liability,
			addition of exclusions, increase in the Deductible, or reduction in the
			<fo:inline font-weight="bold">Policy Period</fo:inline> or duration except a reduction in coverage filed with and
			approved by the Commission and applicable to an entire line,
			classification or subclassification of insurance; and
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-body>
		</fo:list-item>
		<fo:list-item>
		<fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:block>
			(b)
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:list-item-body start-indent="28mm">
		<fo:block>
			“insurer-initiated increase in premium” means an increase in
			premium other than one resulting from changes in: (i) coverage
			requested by the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Named Insured</fo:inline>; (ii) the Limit of Liability requested
			by the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Named Insured</fo:inline>; (iii) the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Insured’s</fo:inline> operation or location that
			results in a change in the classification of the risk; or (iv) the
			rating exposures.
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-body>
		</fo:list-item>
		</fo:list-block>
		</fo:block>
		<fo:block space-after="4mm">
			If the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Insurer</fo:inline> does not provide notice in the manner required in this
			subsection, coverage shall remain in effect until 45 days after written
			notice is given, unless the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Named Insured</fo:inline> obtains replacement coverage
			or elects to cancel sooner in either of which cases coverage under the
			prior policy shall cease on the effective date of the replacement
			coverage or the elected date of cancellation as the case may be. If the
			<fo:inline font-weight="bold">Named Insured</fo:inline> fails to accept or rejects the changed policy, coverage
			for any period that extends beyond the expiration date will under the
			prior policy’s rates, terms and conditions as applied against the
			renewal policy’s limits, rating exposures, and additional coverages. If
			the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Named Insured</fo:inline> accepts the changed policy, the reduction in coverage
			or increase in premium shall take effect upon the expiration of the
			prior policy.
		</fo:block>
		<fo:block space-after="4mm">
			Notice of conditional renewal shall not be required if:
		</fo:block>
		<fo:block space-after="4mm">
		<fo:list-block>
		<fo:list-item>
		<fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:block>
			(a)
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:list-item-body start-indent="28mm">
		<fo:block>
			the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Insurer</fo:inline>, after written demand, has not received, within 45 days
			after such demand has been mailed or delivered to the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Named Insured</fo:inline> at
			the address shown on the policy, or delivered electronically to the
			address provided by the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Named Insured</fo:inline>, sufficient information from the
			<fo:inline font-weight="bold">Named Insured</fo:inline> to provide the required notice;
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-body>
		</fo:list-item>
		<fo:list-item>
		<fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:block>
			(b)
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:list-item-body start-indent="28mm">
		<fo:block>
			such notice is waived in writing by the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Named Insured</fo:inline>;
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-body>
		</fo:list-item>
		</fo:list-block>
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-body>
		</fo:list-item>
		</fo:list-block>
		
		<fo:block margin-top="2cm"/>
           <fo:block  font-size="9px" color="grey" text-align="left">LPL-AMEND-VA (04/17)&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
               &#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
